<p>Zilla Slab and Open Sans are the standard typefaces on mozilla.org websites. Since we design for a global audience, we need to establish some guidelines for fallbacks where these fonts don’t have language support.</p>


<section class="mds-section">

    <h2>Typefaces</h2>

    <h3>Zilla Slab</h3>
    <p>Zilla Slab is our custom brand typeface. We use it for our wordmark and as a display font for headlines. It’s a contemporary slab serif based on Typotheque’s Tesla. Zilla Slab is a free, open source font available for download.</p>

    <div id="specimen-zilla-slab" class="mds-specimen mds-specimen-font">
    {{#with (data "specimens")}}
        {{this.alphabet}}
        {{this.characters}}
        {{this.digits}}
        {{this.punctuation}}
        {{this.special}}
        {{this.currencies}}
    {{/with}}
    </div>

    <p>
        <a class="button button-hollow" href="https://github.com/mozilla/zilla-slab/releases/">Download from Github</a>
        <a class="button button-hollow" href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Zilla+Slab">Use on Google Fonts</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Open Sans</h3>
    <p>Open Sans is more legible than Zilla at small sizes, so it’s our standard typeface for body copy, labels, captions, links, navigation, etc. It’s also used as a header font when the Firefox brand needs to be expressed more than the Mozilla brand. Open Sans is designed by Steve Matteson, and is also an open source font.</p>

    <div id="specimen-open-sans" class="mds-specimen mds-specimen-font">
    {{#with (data "specimens")}}
        {{this.alphabet}}
        {{this.characters}}
        {{this.digits}}
        {{this.punctuation}}
        {{this.special}}
        {{this.currencies}}
    {{/with}}
    </div>

</section>
